Every viral product is actually popular; whenever a new product is launched brands send their products to thousands of influencers to market and this creates the  illusion of virality.
It typically doesn’t mean the product is bad, it can be good but at the same time it doesn’t mean it’s popular.

2. Acne will heal naturally once you hit 22-23; acne doesn’t work this way, it a literal skin condition that needs to be treated under right guidance and using right products.

3. DIY Sunscreen is safe!!! Are we still living in 80s? I can’t believe there are people who still believes in this and actually use it and market it.

4. Toner is optional; toner/ mist are as necessary as any other skincare products. They actually prep your skin so that your other products absorbs properly. Once you start using it there is no back for you.

5. Sunscreen causes cancer🤦‍♀️🤦‍♀️🤦‍♀️ I’m so done with the fear mongering of the sunscreens, when in reality they save your skin from cancer.

6. Skincare is actually ruing your skin; this is actually kinda personal, whenever my skin is breaking out I hear people around me say oh maybe it’s because you use too much skincare. When in reality it can be hormonal or because of the sugar I’m consuming.

Natural skincare is best; excuse me but do you even know the definition of natural? No. Because there isn’t a standard definition of natural.
